147Pm solution in H-Cl acid with total activity 4MBq,
mass 120 ng 147Pm, was mixed with enriched to 98.27%
147Sm as carrier in the form of Sm2-O3 oxide 4 mg
weight, then dried up and mixed with 10 mg of
graphite powder and pressed into a pellets 6 mm
diameter, 0.4 mm thickness. The pellet was then
enclosed in a flat graphite cylinder with 0.3 mm
thick walls. The canned sample was centered on a
standard sample holder consisting of a 0.03 mm thick
kapton foil stretched over a 3 mm thick aluminum ring
with 36 mm inner and 40 mm outer diameter.
Sample mass is 28.7+-1.2 ng ((1.17+-0.05) E+14 atoms),
146Pm admixture is 0.0015%, Nd impurity is 100 mg/l
Sample was sandwiched between two gold foils 6 mm
diameter, 0.03 mm thick mounted in the same way on
Kapton foils and aluminum rings as the 147Pm sample
